comments: Haliburton (SAC) jumps A to B and turns his body to create the contact with Booker (PHX) during his upward shooting motion, which affects his jump shot attempt. Booker does not abandon his shot attempt, nor does he abruptly or overtly launch himself into Haliburton.
Crowder (PHX) moves toward Haliburton (SAC) on his shot contest and any foot to foot contact after the release is deemed marginal as it does not affect Haliburton's ability to follow-through.
Booker (PHX) brings two hands to the ball to stop his dribble at the three point line and then restarts his dribble on the drive to the basket.
Bridges (PHX) avoids making contact with Barnes' (SAC) arm on his dislodge attempt during the shot near the rim.
Paul (PHX) briefly grasps Fox's (SAC) arm and marginal contact occurs as they disengage on the pass.
Crowder (PHX) moves alongside Barnes (SAC) with a resting hand on his back and does not wrap him or affect his FOM.
Crowder (PHX) extends his arm out and marginal contact occurs to Hield's (SAC) arm before the clean ball contact to deflect the pass away.
Crowder (PHX) jumps alongside Barnes (SAC) and avoids making contact to his arm during the contest of his shot near the rim.
At the end of the drive, Booker (PHX) releases from the contact with Hield (SAC) before his step back jump shot attempt.
Hield (SAC) legally contests Booker's (PHX) jump shot attempt and any marginal contact after the release is initiated by Booker's slight leg extension.
Bridges (PHX) commits a take foul on Fox (SAC).
During the inbound, Booker (PHX) grabs and pulls Hield's (SAC) jersey away from his body and affects his FOM.
Hield (SAC) and Johnson (PHX) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Booker (PHX) legally contests Barnes' (SAC) jump shot attempt.
